1.4
log
@replace cross-references to the rand(3) manual that no longer exists
@
text
@d1 2
a2 1
.\"	$OpenBSD: DH_generate_parameters.3,v 1.3 2016/11/12 19:23:16 jmc Exp $
d4 48
a51 1
.Dd $Mdocdate: November 12 2016 $
d113 7
a119 1
It checks that
d121 11
a131 1
is a safe prime, and that
d133 2
a134 9
is a suitable generator.
In the case of an error, the bit flags
.Dv DH_CHECK_P_NOT_SAFE_PRIME
or
.Dv DH_NOT_SUITABLE_GENERATOR
are set in
.Pf * Fa codes .
.Dv DH_UNABLE_TO_CHECK_GENERATOR
is set if the generator cannot be checked, i.e. if it does not equal 2 or 5.
d152 1
a152 1
.Xr DH_free 3 ,
